tldr: The user requested a review and implementation of missing features for a
  sleep questionnaire application. The agent successfully implemented a
  tiredness severity scale, COMISA detection, insufficient sleep syndrome
  detection, outbound links, weighted EDS scoring, full CSV export, and
  pain/chronic fatigue screening.
overview: The user initiated a request to review and enhance a sleep
  questionnaire application. The primary goal was to ensure all acceptance
  criteria from the Statement of Work and detailed questionnaire specification
  were met. The agent systematically addressed several key areas. This included
  adding a 1-10 severity scale for tiredness, implementing detection for
  Comorbid Insomnia and Sleep Apnea (COMISA), and integrating logic for
  Insufficient Sleep Syndrome. Furthermore, the agent enhanced the report
  generation by adding a dedicated "Resources & Next Steps" section with
  relevant outbound links and refined the Excessive Daytime Sleepiness (EDS)
  scoring with weighted calculations. A significant improvement was made to the
  data export functionality, expanding the CSV to include all flattened
  questionnaire responses. Finally, the agent incorporated new questions for
  pain severity and chronic fatigue screening, complete with detection logic and
  tailored recommendations within the report. The implementation involved
  modifying various files, including type definitions, validation schemas, UI
  components, API routes, and report generation logic, ensuring a comprehensive
  update to the application's functionality and reporting capabilities.
